{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Exempt takeaways that operate on or in motorway services from Covid-19 curfews",
        "additional_details": "As a night-time truck driver due to the Covid restrictions on takeaways there is no where we can stop and get hot food. I feel that takeaways that operate inside motorway services or alongside major trunk routes should be given special permission to be able to open so that night truckers who are keeping the country moving can have access to a hot meal and not just some cold day-old over-priced sandwich.",
        "background": "The Government should exempt takeaway venues that operate along our motorway and major trunk network from Covid-19 restrictions on opening hours.",
